{"key":"processedPost-8525518","value":{"id":8525518,"first":8524931,"last":8526025,"when":1213510437,"utime":"06/15/08 09:13 AM","cleanedPost":"<blockquote>Quote:<br />Because manure or even coir/coffee has a better amount of nutes than berries and they contam easily so that is why they are used as a spawn and not a sub. </blockquote><br />Actually, it's the exact opposite.&nbsp; Grains have more 'nutes' than bulk substrates, and that's why grains are used as spawn.<br />The reason we don't mix various grains is because having a uniform grain size makes hydrating to the correct moisture content possible.&nbsp; That's why rye berries and/or rye grass seed will outperform wild bird seed, which is a mix of different sized grains, some of which will be too wet, and others too dry.<br />There is a lot of good to be gained from mixing various bulk substrate materials together, but not grains.<br />RR"}}